    dcterms:creator <urn:markdown:Bildungsroman:person:Auguste%20Rodin>;
    paradicms:collection <urn:markdown:Bildungsroman:collection:Passion>;
    dcterms:abstract "<blockquote>\n<p>Who, if I cried out, would hear me among the Angelic<br />\nOrders? And even if one were to suddenly<br />\ntake me to its heart, I would vanish into its<br />\nstronger existence. For beauty is nothing but<br />\nthe beginning of terror, that we are still able to bear,<br />\nand we revere it so, because it calmly disdains<br />\nto destroy us.</p>\n</blockquote><p>Rainer Maria Rilke, <em>Duino Elegies</em>, translated by <a href=\"https://www.poetryintranslation.com/Admin/Copyright.php\">A.S. Kline</a></p>".
